Manaburn is currently totally usless and as a class defining skill, ruined.  What they could do to allow people to use it again is much like with Lifeburn, Necros get a very fast hp regen, add to the dot componant a way for the wizard to regen about 2 bubbles of mana very quickly after he manaburns.  What they could do is make this cost roughly the same ammount of AAs as the SK harmtouch track.  This would raise the usefullness of the skill back on par with harmtouch and would make wizards actually care about manaburn again <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=68788" target="top">Oxoxo Xoxox ~ Arcanist</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
